{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/centeroffset"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"abstract":[{"text":"The offset, measured in points, at which to place the center of the view.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["occ"],"platforms":["iOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@property"},{"text":" (","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"nonatomic"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@CGVector","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CGVector"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"centerOffset"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"By default, the center point of an annotation view is placed at the geographic","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"coordinate point of the associated annotation. If you do not want the view to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"be centered, you can use this property to reposition the view. The offset’s","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dx"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"dy","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" values are measured in points. Positive offset values move the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"annotation view down and to the right, while negative values move it up and to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the left."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Set the offset if the annotation view’s visual center point is somewhere other"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"than the logical center of the view. For example, the view may contain an image","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"that depicts a downward-pointing pushpin or thumbtack, with the tip positioned"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"at the center-bottom of the view. In that case, you would set the offset’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dx"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to zero and its ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dy"},{"text":" to half the height of the view.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNAnnotationView(py)centerOffset","roleHeading":"Instance Property","title":"centerOffset","remoteSource":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/maplibre\/maplibre-native\/blob\/main\/platform\/ios\/src\/MLNAnnotationView.h#L159","fileName":"MLNAnnotationView.h"},"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"property","fragments":[{"text":"centerOffset","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"centerOffset","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/centerOffset"},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView/centerOffset":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/centeroffset","type":"topic","title":"centerOffset","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/centerOffset","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"centerOffset"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The offset, measured in points, at which to place the center of the view."}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotation":{"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol is used to provide annotation-related information"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to a map view. To use this protocol, you adopt it in any custom objects that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"store or represent annotation data. Each object then serves as the source of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"information about a single map annotation and provides critical information,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"such as the annotation’s location on the map. Annotation objects do not provide"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the visual representation of the annotation but typically coordinate (in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"conjunction with the map view’s delegate) the creation of an appropriate","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"objects to handle the display."}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotation","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNAnnotation"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","role":"symbol","title":"MLNAnnotation","type":"topic"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","title":"MapLibre","abstract":[{"text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling.","type":"text"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","title":"MLNAnnotationView","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" class is responsible for marking a point annotation"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"with a view. Annotation views represent an annotation object, which is an"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"object that corresponds to the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol. When an annotation’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"geographic coordinate is visible in the map view, the map view asks its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"delegate to a corresponding annotation view. If an annotation view is created"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with a reuse identifier, the map view may recycle the view when it goes","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"offscreen."}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"MLNAnnotationView","kind":"identifier"}]}}}